title: For Sale:  Leather Dual Loop Holster and Cartridge Belt
postcontent: Western style brown leather holster and cartridge belt manufactured by Hunter Holster Company. Both items in New Old Stock (NOS) condition: purchased new, never used, stored in a drawer for the last 10 years. The holster and belt are set up for right hand wear, but the holster could be worn on left side for cross draw. The leather holster is in frontier dual loop style, comes with hammer thong and leg tie thong (both removable), and is designed to fit a single action revolver with 7.5" barrel (full barrel coverage). The leather cartridge belt is sized XL (approximate adjustment range is 46-51"), and has 25 sewn-on leather loops to fit .44, .45 and possibly other cartridge sizes. (I have tested it with .44-40 and .45 Long Colt cartridges: both sizes fit well.) This authentically-fashioned leather gear would work very well for a cowboy action shooting participant, a frontier re-enactor, or anyone who simply prefers this classic holster belt style. Both holster and belt are in excellent, unworn condition. Cartridges were once stored in the belt loops for a period of several months: as the brass casings tarnished, they stained the belt leather above and below the loops -- you will see exactly the same tarnish marks on the original 1800s gun belts that this belt is modeled after. See detail photos provided. Please note that the 7.5" barreled revolver and the .44-40 cartridges shown in one photo are not being offered for sale in this post: these items are shown in order to illustrate their fit in this leather gear. Additional photos available on request.Price is $75.00 cash for the holster and belt as a set. This is less than half the price you'd pay in purchasing these items from a retail seller. I will consider selling the holster and belt separately ($40 cash each) if anyone wants to contact me about that possibility. The holster and belt can be viewed/picked up in or near Lynchburg.
